<includeonly>{{#arraymap:{{Category/effective-properties|category={{{category|}}}}}|,|@@prop@@|{{Category/property-row|prop=@@prop@@|page={{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}}}}|\n}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Renders property value rows for a SemanticSchemas category display.

Iterates the effective property list (including inherited) via
`Category/effective-properties`, then delegates per-row rendering to
`Category/property-row` (which handles the default layout + per-property
overrides).

To customize row rendering:
* Change row layout globally: edit `Template:Category/property-row`
* Change layout for one property: create `Template:Category/property-row/<PropName>`
* Change the whole property list: edit `Template:Category/effective-properties`
  (unusual — most users want the per-property or global overrides above)

Parameters:
* category - The category name (without `Category:` prefix)
* page     - The page (or subobject fragment) to read property values
             from; defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
</noinclude>
